<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="805" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Runyon</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister for foreign affairs concurs in all the views expressed in your
                            cipher telegram of yesterday. He still thinks conference unnecessary.
                            Yesterday does not refer to it. Is it to be assumed that it is
                            waived?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Runyon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>